##Wuhan masks sold outside his province behind controversy

Wechat, chinanewsweekly

Function introduction, here is "China News weekly" the head of the weekly gentleman, the influence has the influence you. Come with me to break through the fog, to find the truth, to watch the Times.

The state has put in place a policy

We will encourage enterprises to increase production of goods and materials in short supply

After several twists and turns, finally got through the WECHAT "group purchase" of the boxes of masks, Guangxi Nanning Lian Yu (not his real name) but could not sleep. She can not help wondering, "Henan Manufacturers" production masks, why from Wuhan delivery? Why does the box on the outside of the mask say "relief supplies" ?

On February 14, friends of Lian Yu, who had been entrusted to buy face masks through wechat merchants, raised these issues on Weibo and attracted attention. Public opinion is pointing to the possible sale of relief supplies. The next day, the official Weibo account of the Economic and Technological Development Zones "claimed" the right to explain the incident, saying in a statement that the masks were manufactured by a wuhan-based protective products company after an investigation by the Public Security Bureau of the Wuhan Development Zone (Hannan district) , aid That is not donated by society.

The official did not elaborate on why "relief materials" were written on the packaging and the goods could be shipped out of Wuhan through logistics controls without any obstacles.

"relief materials" from Wuhan

On February 2, dozens of Nanning residents, including Lian Yu, joined a "group purchase" of one-off masks and finally entered the logistics process. After the outbreak, like the rest of the country, Nanning medical supplies are in short supply, and many citizens are facing a "one-size-fits-all" situation.

Lian Yu is in a group purchase group, someone contacted a self-proclaimed can buy masks on behalf of Wang Surname wechat business. A group of friends to buy a total of 100 boxes of Wang Mou mask, each box has 40.

That's $12,800 for 4,000 masks, plus shipping. The average cost of a mask is $3.20, and everyone thinks the price is acceptable.

Most of the delivery stopped, from time to time someone in the group urge, mask to where? And everybody's doubt, also be from see logistics information after beginning. February 3, logistics display "express in Wuhan, Hannan District Hannan business point has been loaded" . In other words, the masks were shipped from Wuhan.

In this regard, wechat business explanation is that "the mask factory is basically Hubei. ".

As the most serious disaster area of the epidemic, Wuhan Hospitals had repeatedly spread out of medical protection materials, even ran out, the gap in civilian masks also exist for many days, every day donated masks from other provinces and cities to Wuhan. And at that time, the mask has been as a "war material" in Hubei Province was unified deployment, most of the mask manufacturers were requisitioned by the government departments, in order to the first time the medical masks sent to the hands of first-line medical staff.

In this case, why can there be masks issued from Wuhan, and sent to the mild epidemic in other provinces and cities? Before the masks were shipped, the businessman, surnamed Wang, had clearly told the buyers that the masks were products exported from the Henan Factory to Japan. And the mask that should Henan dispatch goods, however set out in Wuhan, manufacturer also became Wuhan local manufacturer.

A week later, the masks arrived in Nanning from Wuhan. Before the courier could deliver it, the Public Security Department contacted the buyer first. The reason is very simple, the epidemic area over the mask, for safety reasons, we need to ask.

When several buyers, accompanied by police officers, went to inspect the goods, they saw for the first time the words "relief supplies" written in black ink on the box containing the masks. Those four words have thoroughly unnerved buyers.

The buyer looked at the package and saw the words "relief supplies" written on the box. Photo: Courtesy of the respondents

We let responsible for the purchase of small leaves continue to contact wechat business, ask the source of masks. At the same time, someone through the Express Company learned that since the city of Wuhan closed, there is indeed logistics control. Individual from Wuhan to the field of express delivery, in principle is three kilograms and less.

"there are 2,000 masks in two cases, and the invoice shows that the weight is 22 kilograms. Why can the masks be sent out at this time? " This is the most confusing question for most buyers.

"It's all about connections. "

When the mask was temporarily detained by the Nanning police, lobular was responsible for contacting wechat merchants and mask manufacturers, and then posted it in the group purchase group. He Xiong, the contact person for the mask manufacturer, Foshan, told her: There is no problem with the goods, and the public security has shown the certificate here. However, lobular so far is not clear about the meaning of this sentence.

On February 11, the quality inspection results of the masks in Wuhan showed that the products were qualified, and the quality inspection department returned the masks to the group buyers.

After taking back the mask, everyone was still in doubt. After Lian Yu and a friend posted a query on Weibo, the netizen sensitively questioned whether someone would have used the aid donated by another place to resell it?

The public opinion on the network has alarmed the mask manufacturer. On February 15, he Xiong called Xiaoye, saying that "the Internet is buzzing now, we are very passive, " and said he had been harassed by phone several times in the past two days.

Xiaoye didn't know about Weibo, and she told he Xiong that if you are harassed, you can call the police. "What's the use of reporting a case? We are in a disaster area in Wuhan, and now we are sending masks to other places, which is the target of all arrows, " He Xiong told her.

"Internet users won't let go of the words 'relief materials' , which must have been written by someone else, someone who wants to harm our factory, " he said. He denied that he or the factory had written the words 'relief materials' on the box that contained the mask.

But the courier who delivered the masks had a different story to he. A week ago, these masks were in Hannan District, Wuhan. The delivery boy in charge of the area recalled that there were about 70 or 80 boxes of "relief supplies" that day. "They sent it together, they wrote it themselves, " said the courier.

Wang said the masks were shipped out of Wuhan the next day, the factory's masks "can not be sent out at all, " because "the government supervision there, a shipment to the disaster area. ".

In addition, the wechat business also revealed that now that they are holding masks, they are already "passing one hand over the other. " "I don't know what hand I'm on. I just know it's from my friend's side and he got it from someone else. If you go straight to the manufacturer, you won't get it at all. People get it through their connections and then sell it at a higher price. "

Liu Junhai, director of the Commercial Law Research Institute at Renmin University of China, said that it is not justifiable to sell a large number of masks from the hardest hit areas to other provinces and cities in any case. This violates the period of epidemic prevention and control, the principle of centralized distribution of goods and materials and giving priority to the supply of the worst-hit areas and the first-line areas. "The reason why people were angry when Dali cut off Hu's face mask in Chongqing before is also because of violating this principle. "

On the other hand, he suggested that Wuhan and even Hubei should find out as soon as possible the true supply and demand situation of face masks, "How many masks are needed in the whole of Wuhan and Hubei? How many masks can be produced locally? How many masks have been donated by people at home and abroad? If local production is sufficient, then can foreign countries stop donating? "

The difficulty of manufacturer's production

On February 15th, the second day of public opinion fermenting, "after investigation, he Xiong's mask for sale online came from Wuhan Huashida Protective Products Co. , Ltd. , which produces and exports masks and other protective products... netizens questioned that the mask was produced by Wuhan Huashida Protective Products Co. , Ltd. , not a rescue aid donated by the society, and the company has issued a statement to the district public security sub-bureau about he Xiong's taking the mask from the company on February 1, " the official Weibo account of the Economic and Technological Development Zones said

But such a statement was deemed by netizens to be an understatement, not only did not explain why the box said "relief supplies" , nor did it explain the legitimacy of selling masks, then came the question: "At present, mask production is strictly controlled and requires local authorization, but in Hubei Province, which is in great shortage of materials, there are factories that can start to do micro-commerce. " "The whole world knows that Wuhan lacks masks, and Wuhan can sell them outside. " "If the local production capacity is sufficient, why do volunteers from other places buy the same masks and send them to Hubei? "

The face mask manufacturer at the center of the controversy, Foshan Huashida Protective Products Co. , Ltd. , has been reported by many state media as an advanced enterprise in "fighting against the epidemic" . "As long as the Party and the government call, we promise to return to work indefinitely to produce protective products, " He Zhenhua, the company's general manager, told Xinhua and Guangming Daily, among other media outlets, the company and all its employees agreed to postpone their vacation and put in full production until the outbreak was alleviated.

According to previous media reports, the company can produce 600,000 daily General Medical Masks, N95 masks 5000, high-level protective clothing 2000 pieces. Prior to this, Wuhan Huashida is a specialized export protection products, in the country has not yet obtained a medical device production license. After the outbreak of the disease, the Hubei Provincial Bureau of Market Supervision issued the company with an emergency second-class medical device production license, allowing the enterprise to produce medical protection products in the country.

A source in the industry told China Newsweek that due to the medical needs of the development of the epidemic, many manufacturing enterprises have to incur certain costs to recall their employees during the holidays, "At this time, production is at a loss. In addition to production costs and staff salaries, many companies that produce medical-related supplies and accessories are paying a cost price to the first line. Even so, the money is hard to get back, and the pressure on funds is great. " The insider expressed understanding for the practice of some manufacturers seeking their own sales after being requisitioned.

Such a statement, in the communication between he Xiong and the buyer has been mutually corroborated. He has said that if companies supply the government in its entirety and do not export at all, they will lose money every day. China News Weekly asked he for comment, but did not receive a response.

Prior to this, there have been a number of media reports mask, isolation clothing and other production enterprises at a loss production, or even "a loss of production. ". As a result, the state has also introduced a corresponding subsidy policy. On February 9, the National Development and Reform Commission, the Ministry of Finance and the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology of the People's Republic of China issued a notice to encourage enterprises to increase production and supply of materials needed to deal with the epidemic, the N95 mask and other ten kinds of medical protection products will be purchased by the government. The relevant departments of the state should help enterprises to solve practical difficulties such as capital, qualification, production site, equipment purchase and raw material purchase.

As of press time, Wuhan Huashida Protective Products Co. , Ltd. did not respond to the reasons for the sale of masks. But there may be more to the story than the provenance and whereabouts of the 4,000 masks. "I hope that through this matter, the first is to urge the relevant departments to make a good overall plan, and the second is to truly meet the public's right to know, " Liu said.
